The '''NieR:Automata flowers''' world is a recreation of a location from the 2017 role-playing game [[Wikipedia:Nier:_Automata|NieR:Automata™]], developed by [[Wikipedia:PlatinumGames|PlatinumGames]] and published by [[Wikipedia:Square Enix|Square Enix]]. It is based on the secret area where Kaine's shack is located, which the player encounters at the end of a long series of sidequests.

The world was a very popular{{Citation needed}} hangout location in VRChat, due to its very calm atmosphere, amazing visuals, and beautiful music.

The world is set in a cave whose floor is completely covered in delicate white flowers, known as "Lunar Tears". In the middle of the cave is a shack, with a mirror facing it. Just behind the mirror is a crater with an object buried in it. At the opening of the cave is an elevator, where players spawn.


== Trivia ==
* The song that plays in the world is "[https://youtu.be/Gibu0sJQwkM Kainé (Salvation)]" from the NieR:Automata OST.
* The world contains a number of hidden easter eggs.
* The elevator has a glowing light on it, the colour of which can be changed by pressing the elevator's recall button. This will also cause a single Lunar Tear in the world to glow the same colour.
* One easter egg, once discovered, will cause the particles floating through the air to glow rainbow colours and the song "[https://youtu.be/ifDWI3YbDDk Weight of the World]" from the NieR:Automata OST to play.
* The other easter eggs are related to an old [https://vrclist.com/author/%E2%98%85IDENTITY%E2%98%85 ARG event]
* The object buried in the crater glows when an avatar touches it.
* There are chests scattered around the world. While they gave special items to the player in the original game, most of them are empty in this world.

